WEBVTT

01:46.291 --> 01:47.917
Dexter:
PREVIOUSLY ON "DEXTER"...

01:47.917 --> 01:51.583
Dexter: MY MOTHER -- SHE WAS
MURDERED WHEN I WAS A BOY.

01:51.583 --> 01:53.333
I WAS THERE. I SAW IT.

01:53.333 --> 01:55.417
THERE WERE THREE MEN ARRESTED
FOR THOSE MURDERS.

01:55.417 --> 01:57.458
ONE'S DECEASED, ONE'S DOING LIFE
WITHOUT POSSIBILITY,

01:57.458 --> 01:59.583
AND THAT'S THE ONLY ONE
THAT'S STILL AN OPEN CASE --

01:59.583 --> 02:01.166
SANTOS JIMINEZ.

02:01.166 --> 02:03.250
1972!

02:03.250 --> 02:05.458
DID YOU HAVE TO SAW HER
INTO LITTLE PIECES?

02:05.458 --> 02:07.792
DID YOU HAVE TO LEAVE TWO
LITTLE BOYS SOAKING IN A POOL

02:07.792 --> 02:10.333
OF THEIR MOTHER'S BLOOD?

02:10.333 --> 02:14.917
I DON'T CARE WHAT YOU DID.
IT'S OKAY.

02:17.166 --> 02:18.500
WHO THE FUCK ARE YOU?

02:18.500 --> 02:21.166
OH, PARDON MY TITS.

02:21.166 --> 02:23.041
HOW COULD YOU DO THIS TO RITA,
NOT TO MENTION HER KIDS?

02:23.041 --> 02:25.750
HEY, RITA BROKE UP
WITH ME,  OKAY?

02:25.750 --> 02:27.375
'CAUSE WHEN YOU'RE AROUND,

02:27.375 --> 02:30.000
I KIND OF FEEL LIKE I CAN DEAL
WITH ANYTHING, YOU KNOW?

02:30.000 --> 02:32.667
MORGAN...

02:42.500 --> 02:45.291
YOUR PAST IS A BIGGER MYSTERY
THAN FUCKING JIMMY HOFFA.

02:45.291 --> 02:48.375
IT'S TIME TO MAKE DOAKES
GO AWAY.

02:48.375 --> 02:50.166
AAH!

02:55.333 --> 02:58.083
LaGuerta: SERGEANT DOAKES
IS ON ADMINISTRATIVE LEAVE

02:58.083 --> 02:59.959
PENDING AN INTERNAL AFFAIRS
INVESTIGATION.

03:01.375 --> 03:03.750
THE KILLER'S MAKING US
CHASE OUR TAILS.

03:03.750 --> 03:05.875
YOU KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS?

03:05.875 --> 03:07.166
THAT HE MIGHT BE
ONE OF US?

03:09.291 --> 03:11.959
Lila: I WAS WORKING ON MY PIECE,
AND IT JUST CAUGHT FIRE.

03:11.959 --> 03:13.166
I WAS SO SCARED.

03:13.166 --> 03:15.667
PROMISE ME THAT YOU WON'T
LEAVE ME,

03:15.667 --> 03:17.125
THAT YOU WON'T GO ANYWHERE.

03:17.125 --> 03:18.959
I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

03:29.709 --> 03:31.500
Debra: I CAN'T BELIEVE
HE SAID IT.

03:31.500 --> 03:33.041
EVEN FOR MASUKA,
IT WAS TOO MUCH.

03:33.041 --> 03:34.667
AND BATISTA
DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

03:34.667 --> 03:36.667
TALK ABOUT LAME --
HE FUCKING SAT THERE.

03:36.667 --> 03:38.041
YOU KNOW HOW MUCH
I WANTED TO...

03:38.041 --> 03:41.041
IS THAT THE SPORTS SECTION?

03:41.041 --> 03:43.417
I USED TO ENJOY QUIET MORNINGS,

03:43.417 --> 03:46.542
BUT EVER SINCE THE FIRE
AT LILA'S LOFT,

03:46.542 --> 03:48.834
SHE'S BEEN CRASHING HERE
A BIT TOO OFTEN.

03:48.834 --> 03:49.834
IS THAT MY SHIRT?

03:49.834 --> 03:50.709
I THOUGHT IT WAS DEXTER'S.

03:50.709 --> 03:52.041
IT'S NOT.

03:52.041 --> 03:56.041
UH, NO, IT'S OKAY.
JUST...KEEP IT.

03:56.041 --> 03:59.083
AND SO NOW I SHARE THE KITCHEN
WITH A COBRA AND A MONGOOSE.

03:59.083 --> 04:00.959
DID SOMEBODY  DRINK ALL
THE COFFEE AGAIN?

04:00.959 --> 04:02.959
NO. SOMEBODY DIDN'T  DRINK
ALL THE COFFEE.

04:02.959 --> 04:04.375
I HAD A CUP,
AND DEXTER HAD A CUP,

04:04.375 --> 04:06.333
AND IT JUST KIND OF
WENT LIKE THAT

04:06.333 --> 04:08.625
[ British accent ]
UNTIL THE POT  WAS EMPTY.

04:08.625 --> 04:10.083
DEB, PLEASE.
WHAT?

04:10.083 --> 04:12.125
SOMEONE DIDN'T DRINK ALL
THE COFFEE. STUPID QUESTION.

04:12.125 --> 04:13.625
WHY ARE YOU STICKING UP
FOR HER, ANYWAY?

04:13.625 --> 04:15.291
I'M JUST TRYING
TO KEEP THE PEACE.

04:16.417 --> 04:19.000
MAYBE WE SHOULD STAY
AT YOUR PLACE TONIGHT.

04:19.000 --> 04:21.041
HAS THE FIRE DAMAGE
BEEN REPAIRED YET?

04:21.041 --> 04:23.500
THE INSURANCE COMPANY
IS STILL DICKING ME AROUND.

04:23.500 --> 04:24.542
WON'T GIVE ME A CHECK.

04:24.542 --> 04:26.458
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.
I'LL BE MOVING OUT SOON.

04:26.458 --> 04:28.750
STOP LEECHING OFF YOUR BROTHER?
WHATEVER FOR?

04:28.750 --> 04:31.041
AGAIN, DEX,
THANKS FOR STICKING UP FOR ME.

04:31.041 --> 04:32.208
I AM SWITZERLAND.

04:32.208 --> 04:33.542
YEAH,
AND I'M OUT OF HERE.

04:35.750 --> 04:37.458
[ SIGHS ]

04:41.750 --> 04:44.250
WHAT'S THIS?

04:44.250 --> 04:47.709
[ CHUCKLES ]
IT'S THE DRAGON ZOMBIE.

04:47.709 --> 04:50.083
CODY LIKES TO HIDE THINGS
IN MY BAG.

04:50.083 --> 04:52.041
HE'S TRYING TO CONTROL YOU.

04:52.041 --> 04:54.000
BY HIDING TOYS IN YOUR BAG,

04:54.000 --> 04:56.959
YOU HAVE NO CHOICE
BUT TO RETURN THEM TO HIM.

04:56.959 --> 04:59.667
HE'S 7. HE SELDOM HAS THOUGHTS
MORE COMPLICATED

04:59.667 --> 05:01.208
THAN THE DESIRE FOR CANDY.

05:01.208 --> 05:03.417
I'LL SEE YOU
AT YOUR LOFT TONIGHT.

05:09.041 --> 05:11.667
OH, HONEY -- HONEY, NO.

05:11.667 --> 05:12.917
NO.

05:12.917 --> 05:15.000
YOU SAID WE COULD
MAKE BREAKFAST.

05:15.000 --> 05:17.083
I MEANT CEREAL, BABY.

05:17.083 --> 05:18.291
I DON'T WANT CEREAL.

05:18.291 --> 05:19.834
[ SIGHS ]

05:22.458 --> 05:25.333
I GUESS I SHOULD GIVE RITA
BACK HER KEY.

05:27.792 --> 05:29.291
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

05:32.125 --> 05:34.834
CODY, NO.
NO, LET MOMMY GET THE D--

05:34.834 --> 05:36.041
IT'S DEXTER!

05:36.041 --> 05:37.375
HE BROUGHT DOUGHNUTS!

05:37.375 --> 05:41.000
I DID. I ALSO BROUGHT...
A DRAGON ZOMBIE!

05:41.000 --> 05:42.709
I KNEW YOU'D FIND IT!

05:42.709 --> 05:43.917
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

05:43.917 --> 05:46.667
HOPE IT'S OKAY I'M HERE.

05:46.667 --> 05:49.959
COULD YOU WATCH THEM
WHILE I FINISH GETTING READY?

05:49.959 --> 05:51.875
ASTOR STILL HAS HOMEWORK.

05:59.083 --> 06:03.000
THANK YOU, DEXTER.

06:03.000 --> 06:04.834
MEET ME AT THE CAR.

06:07.667 --> 06:10.250
GOOD THING I DROPPED BY.

06:10.250 --> 06:12.125
DON'T EVER DO IT AGAIN.

06:13.667 --> 06:15.208
I'M SORRY?

06:15.208 --> 06:18.000
IT'S TOO HARD ON THE KIDS,
AND IT'S TOO HARD ON ME.

06:18.000 --> 06:19.834
IT'S PAUL ALL OVER AGAIN.

06:19.834 --> 06:23.375
PLEASE, DEXTER,
JUST STAY AWAY.

06:32.750 --> 06:34.709
YOU'LL NOTICE WE HAVE
SOME NEW FACES HERE.

06:34.709 --> 06:36.041
PLEASE MAKE THEM FEEL WELCOME.

06:36.041 --> 06:39.834
OUR IMMEDIATE TASK IS TO
RE-EXAMINE EVERY CRIMINAL CASE

06:39.834 --> 06:41.458
INVOLVING OUR 18 VICTIMS.

06:41.458 --> 06:43.166
WHERE WOULD YOU LIKE US
TO START?

06:43.166 --> 06:44.542
BY ANSWERING EVERY QUESTION

06:44.542 --> 06:47.083
AS HONESTLY AND WITH AS MUCH
DETAIL AS YOU CAN.

06:47.083 --> 06:50.166
EXCUSE ME, SIR.
ANSWERING QUESTIONS?

06:50.166 --> 06:51.709
THAT IS CORRECT.

06:51.709 --> 06:54.458
I CAN HARDLY EXPECT YOU
TO INVESTIGATE YOUR OWN CASES.

06:54.458 --> 06:58.375
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?
ARE WE UNDER INVESTIGATION?

06:58.375 --> 07:00.333
WE ARE NOW OPERATING
UNDER THE ASSUMPTION

07:00.333 --> 07:02.667
THAT OUR KILLER IS SOMEHOW
CONNECTED TO LAW ENFORCEMENT.

07:02.667 --> 07:05.542
WHETHER HE BE A FILE CLERK,
A DISPATCH OFFICER,

07:05.542 --> 07:07.917
PARK RANGER...
OR A POLICE OFFICER.

07:07.917 --> 07:09.834
OR A POLICE OFFICER.

07:09.834 --> 07:12.333
IS THAT WHY YOU BROUGHT IN
ALL THESE SUITS?

07:12.333 --> 07:13.583
SPECIAL AGENTS.

07:13.583 --> 07:16.166
SIR, YOU RISK ALIENATING
EVERY COP ON THE TASK FORCE

07:16.166 --> 07:17.709
IF YOU DO THIS.

07:17.709 --> 07:20.583
WE GO WHERE THE CHASE
LEADS US...

07:20.583 --> 07:23.542
EVEN IF IT GETS MESSY.

07:28.583 --> 07:29.667
IT'S INSULTING.

07:29.667 --> 07:31.792
WE'RE JUST AS CAPABLE
AS THEY ARE

07:31.792 --> 07:33.583
OF LOOKING
INTO OUR OWN CASES.

07:33.583 --> 07:36.041
WHO WEARS A WOOL SUIT IN
THE MIDDLE OF SUMMER IN MIAMI?

07:36.041 --> 07:38.417
NAZIS -- THAT'S WHO.
IT'S ALL ABOUT INTIMIDATION.

07:38.417 --> 07:40.834
AND THE IDEA THAT ONE OF US
COULD BE THE KILLER?

07:40.834 --> 07:42.083
IT'S COMPLETE BULLSHIT.

07:42.083 --> 07:45.166
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
"US" WHO?

07:45.166 --> 07:48.083
LUNDY HAS HIS FEDS INVESTIGATING
ALL OF OUR CASES

07:48.083 --> 07:50.041
THAT ARE TIED
TO THE BAY HARBOR VICTIMS.

07:50.041 --> 07:51.667
THAT'S GOOD HERE.

07:52.750 --> 07:54.625
LOOK, WE GOT TO
STAND TOUGH HERE.

07:54.625 --> 07:56.250
WE GOT TO MAKE IT CLEAR
TO THEM

07:56.250 --> 07:57.542
THAT WE'RE NOT GONNA BE

07:57.542 --> 07:59.500
THEIR LITTLE "YES, SIR, NO, SIR"
LAPDOGS.

08:01.834 --> 08:03.542
GENTLEMEN.

08:03.542 --> 08:06.792
MORGAN, I'D LIKE TO GO OVER
SOME OF YOUR CASES TOMORROW.

08:06.792 --> 08:08.333
GOT THEM ALL LISTED
RIGHT THERE.

08:08.333 --> 08:10.166
IT WOULD BE HELPFUL
IF YOU COULD GATHER UP

08:10.166 --> 08:11.917
ANY NOTES
YOU MAY HAVE TAKEN.

08:11.917 --> 08:13.500
HAPPY TO HELP.

08:17.250 --> 08:19.250
WAY TO STAND TOUGH,
DEXTER.

08:19.250 --> 08:20.291
SORRY.

08:20.291 --> 08:23.291
THAT'S EXACTLY
HOW HITLER WALKED.

08:27.625 --> 08:29.041
IT SEEMS MY MANIFESTO

08:29.041 --> 08:31.917
UNINTENTIONALLY HELPED LUNDY
NARROW HIS FOCUS.

08:31.917 --> 08:34.834
THAT'S WHAT I GET FOR TRYING
TO EMULATE LILA

08:34.834 --> 08:36.333
AND TAKE THE OFFENSIVE.

08:36.333 --> 08:38.834
I'VE ALWAYS WORKED BEST
IN THE SHADOWS,

08:38.834 --> 08:41.250
AND THAT'S WHERE I HAVE
TO STAY.

08:41.250 --> 08:43.709
LUNDY'S REALLY PISSING
PEOPLE OFF.

08:43.709 --> 08:47.333
HE'S GOT HIS WHOLE CREW
LOOKING THROUGH EVERY CASE

08:47.333 --> 08:49.667
INVOLVING ANY OF
THE BAY HARBOR VICTIMS.

08:49.667 --> 08:51.333
[ CHUCKLES ]
HE SOUNDS DESPERATE.

08:51.333 --> 08:53.500
YOU KNOW YOU'RE GONNA BE
CALLED IN.

08:53.500 --> 08:55.834
I'LL BE CURIOUS TO SEE
IF I SHOW UP.

08:55.834 --> 08:59.625
OKAY, JAMES, YOU NEED TO BE
A LITTLE CAREFUL HERE.

08:59.625 --> 09:02.667
IF YOU WANT TO KEEP YOUR JOB,
YOU GOT TO COOPERATE.

09:02.667 --> 09:05.375
BEING ON SUSPENSION DOES NOT
EXCLUDE YOU FROM THIS.

09:05.375 --> 09:07.208
AND WHO WAS IT
THAT SUSPENDED ME AGAIN?

09:07.208 --> 09:08.583
OH, SHIT.
THAT WAS YOU.

09:08.583 --> 09:11.709
PLEASE, DON'T ACT LIKE
YOU DIDN'T DESERVE IT.

09:11.709 --> 09:13.709
YOUR CASE IS COMING UP
FOR REVIEW IN A WEEK.

09:13.709 --> 09:15.417
IF YOU WANT TO KEEP
YOUR JOB --

09:15.417 --> 09:16.667
YOU KEEP SAYING THAT,
MARIA.

09:16.667 --> 09:18.792
WHAT MAKES YOU THINK I WANT
TO KEEP MY JOB?

09:18.792 --> 09:20.000
WHOA.

09:20.000 --> 09:22.333
ARE YOU JUST TALKING HERE,

09:22.333 --> 09:25.166
OR IS THIS SOMETHING THAT
YOU'VE SERIOUSLY CONSIDERED?

09:25.166 --> 09:26.667
WELL, YOU AND I BOTH KNOW

09:26.667 --> 09:29.291
THAT I'VE GONE AS HIGH
AS I CAN OVER THERE.

09:29.291 --> 09:32.083
MAYBE IT'S TIME TO MOVE ON.

09:32.083 --> 09:34.875
WELL, WHAT WOULD YOU DO?

09:34.875 --> 09:38.041
I DON'T KNOW.
MY FATHER WAS A BUTCHER.

09:38.041 --> 09:40.000
MAYBE I'LL OPEN UP
MY OWN BUTCHER SHOP.

09:40.000 --> 09:43.667
YEAH, I CAN JUST SEE YOU PUTTING
ON AN APRON EVERY MORNING.

09:43.667 --> 09:45.583
[ LAUGHS ]

09:45.583 --> 09:47.750
LOOK, I HAVE A FRIEND.

09:47.750 --> 09:50.667
HE'S THE HEAD OF PERSONNEL
AT STILLWATER SECURITY.

09:50.667 --> 09:51.959
GOVERNMENT CONTRACTORS?

09:51.959 --> 09:54.375
THEY'RE ALWAYS LOOKING
FOR PEOPLE LIKE YOU.

09:54.375 --> 09:55.959
IT'S A DANGEROUS WORLD
OUT THERE.

09:55.959 --> 09:58.291
THEY PAY A LOT OF MONEY
TO MAKE IT SAFE.

09:58.291 --> 09:59.792
YEAH, YOU GOT THAT RIGHT.

09:59.792 --> 10:04.083
ALL RIGHT. SET IT UP.
I'LL MEET WITH YOUR GUY.

10:04.083 --> 10:06.792
OFFICER MORGAN.
DEBRA.

10:06.792 --> 10:08.542
YES?

10:08.542 --> 10:11.667
I PICKED THE RODRIGO CASE
FOR YOU TO LOOK INTO --

10:11.667 --> 10:13.417
SMALL-TIME DOPE DEALER.

10:13.417 --> 10:16.750
ARRESTED FOR MURDER,
ENDED UP WALKING FREE,

10:16.750 --> 10:18.625
THEN DISAPPEARED OFF THE FACE
OF THE EARTH

10:18.625 --> 10:21.333
UNTIL HIS BODY WAS FOUND
IN A GARBAGE BAG IN THE OCEAN.

10:21.333 --> 10:23.208
OH.

10:23.208 --> 10:25.458
NOT EXCITING ENOUGH
FOR YOU?

10:25.458 --> 10:28.000
WELL,
IT'S JUST...I'M HOMICIDE.

10:28.000 --> 10:30.000
I MEAN, I THOUGHT
YOU DIDN'T WANT US

10:30.000 --> 10:31.583
CHECKING INTO OUR OWN CASES.

10:31.583 --> 10:32.959
YOU'RE NEW TO HOMICIDE.

10:32.959 --> 10:35.291
AT THE TIME OF THIS CASE,
YOU WERE STILL IN VICE.

10:35.291 --> 10:36.959
NO CONFLICT THERE.

10:36.959 --> 10:40.291
WELL, I'M FLATTERED YOU WANT ME
IN ON THIS, BUT...

10:40.291 --> 10:42.583
BATISTA AND DOAKES
WERE LEAD HERE.

10:42.583 --> 10:46.125
I FEEL KIND OF WEIRD ABOUT
INVESTIGATING MY OWN COLLEAGUES.

10:46.125 --> 10:47.792
WEIRD. GOSH.

10:47.792 --> 10:50.291
I'D HATE FOR YOU
TO FEEL WEIRD.

10:50.291 --> 10:52.750
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

10:56.375 --> 11:00.333
WOULD YOU HAVE DINNER WITH ME
TOMORROW NIGHT?

11:00.333 --> 11:03.583
OR WOULD THAT MAKE YOU
FEEL WEIRD?

11:06.417 --> 11:09.166
I'D LOVE TO HAVE DINNER
WITH YOU.

11:09.166 --> 11:10.834
GOOD.

11:10.834 --> 11:13.375
I'LL TAKE YOU TO THE BEST
RESTAURANT IN MIAMI.

11:13.375 --> 11:16.000
WOW. GREAT.

11:26.709 --> 11:29.875
[ LILA COUGHS ]

11:29.875 --> 11:34.750
I LIKE THE SMELL.
DON'T YOU?

11:34.750 --> 11:36.875
LIKE SOMETHING EXCITING
HAPPENED HERE.

11:36.875 --> 11:39.166
IT'S LIKE WHEN A PIECE OF BREAD
GETS STUCK IN THE TOASTER.

11:39.166 --> 11:40.917
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:40.917 --> 11:44.125
YOU LIKE TO PRETEND
THERE'S NO POETRY IN YOU.

11:44.125 --> 11:46.458
SO, WHAT'S THE PROBLEM
WITH THE INSURANCE COMPANY?

11:46.458 --> 11:49.291
WHY AREN'T THEY PAYING?

11:49.291 --> 11:50.625
IT'S RIDICULOUS.

11:50.625 --> 11:54.625
THEY THINK THE FIRE
IS OF SUSPICIOUS ORIGIN,

11:54.625 --> 11:57.542
AND THEY NEED TO FINISH
THEIR INVESTIGATION.

11:57.542 --> 11:59.000
WHAT DO THEY MEAN,
"SUSPICIOUS"?

11:59.000 --> 12:01.709
ARE THEY SAYING YOU STARTED
THE FIRE ON PURPOSE?

12:01.709 --> 12:03.875
WHO KNOWS
WHAT THEY'RE SAYING?

12:03.875 --> 12:05.542
YOU KNOW
INSURANCE COMPANIES --

12:05.542 --> 12:08.208
ANYTHING TO KEEP
FROM PAYING OUT.

12:13.542 --> 12:19.250
YEAH, ESPECIALLY WHEN A FIRE
HAS MULTIPLE POINTS OF ORIGIN.

12:21.208 --> 12:23.625
SO, YOU NEVER TOLD ME.

12:23.625 --> 12:27.834
HOW DID IT GO AT RITA'S
THIS MORNING?

12:27.834 --> 12:30.542
UH, YOU KNOW,
I JUST RETURNED CODY'S TOY,

12:30.542 --> 12:32.583
AND THAT WAS IT.

12:32.583 --> 12:34.917
NO QUICKIE
ON THE KITCHEN TABLE?

12:34.917 --> 12:37.083
RITA DOESN'T HAVE
A KITCHEN TABLE.

12:37.083 --> 12:40.083
OH, CLEVER WAY OF NOT ANSWERING
THE QUESTION.

12:40.083 --> 12:42.750
IT WAS...

12:42.750 --> 12:45.417
AWKWARD, ACTUALLY.

12:45.417 --> 12:47.917
ALWAYS IS.

12:47.917 --> 12:51.208
YOU CAN'T GO BACK.
YOU KNOW THAT.

12:51.208 --> 12:53.375
I'M NOT TRYING
TO GO ANYWHERE.

12:53.375 --> 12:56.375
WELL, THE BED'S ALL READY.

12:56.375 --> 12:59.291
UH, I CAN'T.

12:59.291 --> 13:01.542
AND WHY WOULD THAT BE?

13:01.542 --> 13:02.917
I HAVE TOO MUCH WORK TO DO.

13:02.917 --> 13:04.625
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

13:04.625 --> 13:07.583
I HAVE ALL THESE CASE FILES
I HAVE TO GO OVER FOR TOMORROW.

13:07.583 --> 13:09.875
YOU DIDN'T BRING ANY WORK
WITH YOU?

13:09.875 --> 13:14.500
HOME.
I NEED TO...WORK AT HOME.

13:15.917 --> 13:17.083
OKAY.

13:17.083 --> 13:19.291
GOODBYE, THEN.

13:19.291 --> 13:20.917
SO, I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW?

13:22.792 --> 13:24.250
WHATEVER.

13:41.458 --> 13:44.959
IS IT POSSIBLE SHE STARTED
THAT FIRE ON PURPOSE?

13:44.959 --> 13:46.291
I CAN'T IMAGINE WHY.

13:46.291 --> 13:50.000
WHAT I DO KNOW IS THAT I CAN'T
TAKE ANY RISKS RIGHT NOW.

14:05.291 --> 14:06.500
HI, YOU WANTED TO --

14:06.500 --> 14:08.750
MORGAN, COME IN.

14:08.750 --> 14:11.542
CAN I OFFER YOU SOME TEA?

14:11.542 --> 14:14.250
UH, NO, THANK YOU.
I'M...

14:14.250 --> 14:15.792
AND HE POURS IT ANYWAY.

14:15.792 --> 14:18.208
HE'S TRYING TO THROW ME
OFF BALANCE,

14:18.208 --> 14:21.917
SHOW THAT I DON'T HAVE
THE POWER TO SAY NO TO HIM.

14:21.917 --> 14:24.250
HOW ABOUT SOME SESAME CRACKERS
TO GO WITH THAT?

14:24.250 --> 14:25.709
SO I'LL SAY YES TO EVERYTHING.

14:25.709 --> 14:26.959
I'D LOVE SOME.

14:29.000 --> 14:33.000
OH. SORRY.
GUESS I ATE THEM ALL.

14:33.000 --> 14:34.750
ASSHOLE.

14:34.750 --> 14:37.458
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

14:37.458 --> 14:41.041
SO, YOU WORKED
FIRSTHAND ON,

14:41.041 --> 14:42.792
WHAT, FOUR OF THE CASES

14:42.792 --> 14:45.375
RELATED TO THE BAY HARBOR
INVESTIGATION?

14:45.375 --> 14:47.375
I BELIEVE SO.

14:47.375 --> 14:50.208
YOUR REPORTS WERE
A REAL PLEASURE TO READ.

14:50.208 --> 14:51.875
OH?

14:51.875 --> 14:55.375
CONCISE, METICULOUS.
I APPRECIATE THAT.

14:55.375 --> 14:57.250
GOOD. THANK YOU.

14:57.250 --> 15:00.000
DOES YOUR SISTER PREFER MEAT
OR FISH?

15:00.000 --> 15:01.750
DEBRA?

15:01.750 --> 15:04.125
YOU HAVE MORE THAN ONE?

15:04.125 --> 15:06.208
SISTER?

15:06.208 --> 15:08.208
UH, NO. JUST DEB.

15:08.208 --> 15:11.583
OR IS SHE MORE OF A SALAD
KIND OF PERSON?

15:11.583 --> 15:14.792
SHE'S DEFINITELY
A CARNIVORE.

15:14.792 --> 15:16.667
GOOD.

15:16.667 --> 15:19.125
GOOD.

15:19.125 --> 15:22.834
SO...THE RODRIGO CASE.

15:22.834 --> 15:24.458
LET'S TALK ABOUT THAT ONE.

15:24.458 --> 15:25.834
OKAY.

15:25.834 --> 15:27.709
KIND OF BLEW IT,
DIDN'T YOU?

15:29.250 --> 15:30.542
I'M SORRY?

15:30.542 --> 15:31.917
ANTHONY RODRIGO --

15:31.917 --> 15:33.458
CRACK DEALER
WITH AN APPARENT HABIT

15:33.458 --> 15:35.875
OF KILLING PEOPLE
WHO GOT IN HIS WAY.

15:35.875 --> 15:41.125
I BELIEVE THIS WAS -- YES --
DOAKES' AND BATISTA'S CASE.

15:41.125 --> 15:43.834
THEY FINALLY TIED RODRIGO TO ONE
OF HIS VICTIMS,

15:43.834 --> 15:45.917
BUILT A SOLID
MANSLAUGHTER CASE,

15:45.917 --> 15:48.500
WOULD HAVE GOT HIM OFF
THE STREET FOR A FEW YEARS.

15:48.500 --> 15:52.875
BUT THE CASE LARGELY RESTED
ON THE BLOODWORK THAT YOU DID.

15:52.875 --> 15:54.333
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

15:54.333 --> 15:56.834
BLOODWORK THAT IN THE COURSE
OF THE TRIAL

15:56.834 --> 16:00.792
WAS PROVEN TO BE,
WELL...WRONG.

16:00.792 --> 16:05.792
SO, YOU --
ONE OF THE MOST CAUTIOUS

16:05.792 --> 16:07.250
AND PRECISE
FORENSIC SPECIALISTS

16:07.250 --> 16:09.000
I'VE HAD THE PLEASURE
TO WORK WITH --

16:09.000 --> 16:10.625
YOU PERFORMED BLOODWORK

16:10.625 --> 16:13.667
THAT DIRECTLY LED TO RODRIGO
WALKING FREE.

16:13.667 --> 16:18.917
I ASKED MYSELF,
"HOW THE HELL DID THAT HAPPEN?"

16:18.917 --> 16:21.542
AND DID YOU ANSWER, "DEXTER
BLEW THE CASE ON PURPOSE

16:21.542 --> 16:24.125
"SO THAT HE COULD GET RODRIGO
OFF THE STREETS FOR GOOD

16:24.125 --> 16:28.208
WITH A CORDLESS
RECIPROCATING SAW"?

16:28.208 --> 16:30.709
I'M SORRY. YOU'VE CAUGHT ME
OFF-GUARD HERE.

16:30.709 --> 16:33.583
SLOPPY BLOODWORK.

16:36.291 --> 16:40.125
LOOK, THIS WASN'T MY IDEA.

16:40.125 --> 16:42.709
COULD HAVE SAID NO.

16:42.709 --> 16:45.083
COME ON, ANGEL,
WE HAVE A JOB TO DO.

16:45.083 --> 16:46.834
SINCE WHEN IS IT MY JOB
TO TRY AND PROVE

16:46.834 --> 16:49.166
TO A FELLOW POLICE OFFICER
THAT I'M NOT A SERIAL KILLER?

16:49.166 --> 16:50.667
YOU KNOW THAT'S NOT
WHAT THIS IS ABOUT.

16:50.667 --> 16:51.667
WHAT IS THIS ABOUT?

16:51.667 --> 16:53.166
IT'S ABOUT TRYING
TO FIND SOMEONE

16:53.166 --> 16:56.333
WHO HAD MOTIVE AND OPPORTUNITY
TO KILL ALL 18 OF OUR VICTIMS.

16:56.333 --> 16:58.709
UM, NO WAY IT'S ANYBODY
IN OUR DEPARTMENT.

16:58.709 --> 17:00.667
THEN HELP ME PROVE IT.

17:00.667 --> 17:02.875
GO THROUGH THE RODRIGO CASE
WITH ME.

17:02.875 --> 17:04.500
LOOK, IT IS NOT JUST YOU.

17:04.500 --> 17:06.625
LaGUERTA'S COOPERATING
ON HER OLD CASES.

17:06.625 --> 17:08.458
EVEN MATTHEWS
IS COMING IN.

17:18.667 --> 17:20.667
THE RODRIGO FILE.

17:22.333 --> 17:24.083
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:24.083 --> 17:27.542
YOU JUST HAPPEN TO HAVE IT
WITH YOU.

17:27.542 --> 17:30.250
I'M A REASONABLE MAN.

17:34.166 --> 17:35.375
YOU KNOW HOW IT IS.

17:35.375 --> 17:38.875
THE DEFENSE ATTORNEYS BRING IN
THEIR SO-CALLED BLOOD EXPERTS

17:38.875 --> 17:40.750
TO COUNTER EVERYTHING I SAY.

17:40.750 --> 17:42.542
I'M FAMILIAR
WITH THE PROCESS.

17:42.542 --> 17:45.500
I UNDERSTAND HOW THIS MAY LOOK
LIKE SLOPPY BLOODWORK

17:45.500 --> 17:46.709
TO THE LAYMAN.

17:46.709 --> 17:49.750
THAT'S WHAT RODRIGO'S DEFENSE
CONVINCED THE JURY OF.

17:49.750 --> 17:51.333
BUT AS YOU CAN SEE,

17:51.333 --> 17:55.333
THE LOW-VELOCITY BLOOD DROPS
CLEARLY POINT IN THE DIRECTION

17:55.333 --> 17:58.000
OPPOSITE TO THAT IN WHICH
WE KNOW RODRIGO TO HAVE FLED,

17:58.000 --> 17:59.834
WHICH MAKES IT
IMPOSSIBLE --

17:59.834 --> 18:01.375
EXCEPT
THOSE LOW-VELOCITY DROPS

18:01.375 --> 18:04.208
WERE REVEALED TO ACTUALLY BE
90-DEGREE PASSIVE DROPS

18:04.208 --> 18:05.500
THAT WERE GIVEN TAILS

18:05.500 --> 18:07.041
DUE TO THE ANGLE
OF THE FLOOR.

18:10.291 --> 18:14.250
PERHAPS, BUT IF YOU THEN
EXAMINE THE BLOOD TRAIL --

18:14.250 --> 18:16.083
WHICH WE KNOW
ISN'T A BLOOD TRAIL,

18:16.083 --> 18:18.041
BUT PROJECTED BLOOD.

18:18.041 --> 18:20.875
YOU'RE NOT WINNING ME
OVER HERE, MORGAN.

18:24.750 --> 18:26.458
[ SIGHS ]

18:33.458 --> 18:36.250
THE TRUTH?

18:36.250 --> 18:39.208
BY ALL MEANS.

18:41.583 --> 18:43.375
[ SIGHS ]

18:43.375 --> 18:44.667
I WAS OVERWORKED.

18:44.667 --> 18:47.125
I WAS CARRYING HALF A DOZEN
CASES AT ONCE.

18:47.125 --> 18:51.291
IT WAS A HEAT WAVE --
MEANS A SPIKE IN...HOMICIDES.

18:52.875 --> 18:55.000
THIS ONE GOT PUSHED ASIDE.

18:55.000 --> 18:59.750
I DIDN'T WRITE UP MY SUMMARY
UNTIL AN HOUR BEFORE THE TRIAL.

18:59.750 --> 19:02.875
I OBVIOUSLY OVERLOOKED
A FEW THINGS.

19:02.875 --> 19:05.959
A MURDERER WALKED FREE

19:05.959 --> 19:08.542
BECAUSE
YOU WERE OVERWORKED?

19:08.542 --> 19:10.333
YES.

19:23.250 --> 19:25.834
WHO'S THIS GUY?
LENNY ASHER.

19:25.834 --> 19:28.041
LENNY? HE'S A NUTJOB...

19:28.041 --> 19:30.083
BUT IT SAYS HE LIVED
NEXT DOOR TO RODRIGO,

19:30.083 --> 19:31.208
FILED ALL KINDS
OF COMPLAINTS.

19:31.208 --> 19:33.917
BUT HE FILED COMPLAINTS
ABOUT EVERYBODY.

19:33.917 --> 19:35.917
HE'D JUST SIT AT HIS WINDOW
ALL DAY

19:35.917 --> 19:38.375
AND CALL US EVERY TIME
HE SAW SOMEONE MOVE.

19:38.375 --> 19:40.792
HE CALLED US ONCE TO SAY
THERE WAS SOMETHING WEIRD

19:40.792 --> 19:43.166
ABOUT THE CLOUDS.

19:43.166 --> 19:45.792
STILL NO HARM TALKING
TO HIM, RIGHT?

19:47.834 --> 19:49.834
LENNY ASHER?

19:49.834 --> 19:52.417
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?

19:52.417 --> 19:55.000
DETECTIVE BATISTA.
THIS IS OFFICER MORGAN.

19:55.000 --> 19:57.000
WE'RE WITH THE MIAMI
METRO HOMICIDE.

19:57.000 --> 19:59.291
CAN WE COME IN?

20:05.667 --> 20:07.500
WHO'S DEAD?

20:07.500 --> 20:08.750
ANTHONY RODRIGO.

20:08.750 --> 20:12.083
[ Chuckling ] I KNOW.
THEY FOUND HIM IN THE OCEAN.

20:12.083 --> 20:14.667
I HOPE A WHALE ATE HIM
AND SHAT HIM OUT,

20:14.667 --> 20:16.834
AND THEN ATE HIM AGAIN.

20:16.834 --> 20:18.583
YOU WEREN'T TOO CLOSE
TO HIM, WERE YOU?

20:18.583 --> 20:20.291
HE WAS SCUM!

20:20.291 --> 20:23.417
YEAH, YOU MADE NUMEROUS CALLS
ABOUT HIM

20:23.417 --> 20:25.375
WHEN HE USED TO LIVE HERE.

20:25.375 --> 20:27.125
HE WAS A DRUG DEALER.

20:27.125 --> 20:32.041
HE PLAYED LOUD  MUSIC,
URINATED ON MY LILIES.

20:32.041 --> 20:33.500
YOU ACTUALLY SAW THAT?

20:33.500 --> 20:36.917
THEY WERE DEAD.
THAT'S ALL I  NEEDED TO KNOW.

20:36.917 --> 20:39.041
ANY THOUGHTS AS TO WHO
MIGHT HAVE KILLED HIM?

20:39.041 --> 20:41.750
HOW THE HELL
SHOULD I KNOW?

20:41.750 --> 20:47.000
LOOK AT THAT JOKER PARKED RIGHT
IN FRONT OF THE FIRE HYDRANT.

20:47.000 --> 20:49.875
I GOT HIS LICENSE PLATE,
THOUGH.

20:49.875 --> 20:53.208
UM...
THAT WOULD BE OUR CAR.

20:57.208 --> 20:59.250
YOU, UH,
TAKE A LOT OF NOTES?

20:59.250 --> 21:01.583
ANYTHING HINKY HAPPENS
OUTSIDE THIS WINDOW,

21:01.583 --> 21:02.625
I MAKE A NOTE ON IT.

21:02.625 --> 21:04.291
HOW LONG YOU BEEN
DOING THAT?

21:04.291 --> 21:06.583
SINCE SOMEONE STUCK A NAIL
IN MY TIRE --

21:06.583 --> 21:08.875
MARCH 1998.

21:08.875 --> 21:11.375
RODRIGO WAS LAST SEEN ALIVE
THE DAY AFTER HIS TRIAL --

21:11.375 --> 21:12.959
APRIL 16, 2002.

21:12.959 --> 21:15.667
THINK YOU MIGHT HAVE TAKEN
ANY NOTES THAT DAY?

21:15.667 --> 21:17.750
IF SOMETHING HAPPENED,
I DID.

21:17.750 --> 21:19.875
YOU STILL HAVE
THOSE NOTES?

21:27.667 --> 21:30.458
HERE. 2002.

21:32.792 --> 21:35.333
WHAT KIND OF ORDER
DID YOU PUT THEM IN?

21:35.333 --> 21:38.417
I TOLD YOU -- 2002.

21:41.250 --> 21:46.000
I HAVE NO IDEA IF LUNDY
BOUGHT MY EXCUSE.

21:46.000 --> 21:47.917
EITHER WAY,
IT MAKES ME A LITTLE ANXIOUS

21:47.917 --> 21:51.083
TO SEE MY SISTER LOOKING
THROUGH THE RODRIGO FILES --

21:51.083 --> 21:53.583
LOOKING FOR ME.

21:53.583 --> 21:56.291
HEY. DEX.

21:56.291 --> 21:57.959
YOU'RE NEVER GONNA GUESS
WHAT I FOUND.

21:57.959 --> 22:00.709
WHAT DID YOU FIND?

22:00.709 --> 22:03.792
AN APARTMENT.

22:03.792 --> 22:06.917
OH.
[ CHUCKLES ] GREAT.

22:06.917 --> 22:09.041
ONE-BEDROOM NEAR 78th
AND HARDING.

22:09.041 --> 22:11.625
WOW. BIG CHANGE.

22:11.625 --> 22:14.709
YEAH, WELL,
IT'S TIME, YOU KNOW?

22:14.709 --> 22:16.500
WELL, GOOD FOR YOU.
WHEN DO YOU MOVE?

22:16.500 --> 22:18.375
AS SOON AS POSSIBLE,
BUT NOT TONIGHT.

22:18.375 --> 22:19.792
I HAVE A DATE.

22:19.792 --> 22:22.208
I THOUGHT YOU BROKE UP
WITH GABRIEL.

22:22.208 --> 22:26.166
NO, IT'S...SOMEONE NEW.

22:26.166 --> 22:27.875
Lundy.

22:31.166 --> 22:33.834
LUNDY,
SPECIAL AGENT LUNDY?

22:33.834 --> 22:36.166
HE'S AT LEAST 20 YEARS OLDER
THAN ME.

22:36.166 --> 22:37.500
WHAT DO YOU CARE?

22:39.959 --> 22:41.166
I DON'T.

22:41.166 --> 22:42.959
I MEAN...

22:45.417 --> 22:47.834
...I'M SURE YOU WOULDN'T DO
ANYTHING LIKE THAT.

22:47.834 --> 22:50.375
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
DO ANYTHING LIKE WHAT?

22:50.375 --> 22:52.750
LIKE TRY TO SLEEP YOUR WAY
TO THE TOP.

22:52.750 --> 22:55.166
YOU DOUCHE.

22:55.166 --> 22:56.834
THAT IS SO  NOT TRUE.

22:56.834 --> 22:58.083
NO, OF COURSE NOT.

22:58.083 --> 23:00.125
I SHOULDN'T HAVE EVEN
SAID ANYTHING,

23:00.125 --> 23:01.375
AND I'M SURE THAT THOUGHT

23:01.375 --> 23:03.417
WOULD NEVER  EVEN OCCUR
TO ANYONE ELSE.

23:03.417 --> 23:04.875
DOUBLE DOUCHE!

23:04.875 --> 23:08.041
YOU ARE NOT ALLOWED TO TALK
ABOUT ANYONE I DATE

23:08.041 --> 23:11.375
AS LONG YOU'RE SEEING
LITTLE MISS "PARDON MY TITS."

23:11.375 --> 23:14.625
I AM SORRY, DEX,
BUT SHE IS GROSS...

23:14.625 --> 23:17.792
AND PALE,
AND NOBODY IS PALE IN MIAMI.

23:17.792 --> 23:20.166
SHE IS OBVIOUSLY A VAMPIRE.

23:20.166 --> 23:24.875
A GROSS ENGLISH-TITTY
VAMPIRE.

23:24.875 --> 23:28.500
YOU JUST DESCRIBED
THE PERFECT WOMAN.

23:31.709 --> 23:34.083
TRUTH IS I NEED TO AVOID
LILA FOR NOW.

23:34.083 --> 23:36.375
HARRY TAUGHT ME
THAT THE KEY TO SURVIVAL

23:36.375 --> 23:38.166
WAS STAYING ONE STEP AHEAD.

23:38.166 --> 23:40.375
BUT LUNDY ALMOST
TRAPPED ME TODAY.

23:40.375 --> 23:42.625
I CAN'T BE UNPREPARED
LIKE THAT AGAIN.

23:42.625 --> 23:45.041
HEY, IT'S ME.

23:45.041 --> 23:49.000
WHY AREN'T YOU HERE?
I'M STARVING.

23:49.000 --> 23:52.583
OH, I THOUGHT YOU KNEW --
IT'S MY BOWLING NIGHT.

23:52.583 --> 23:54.417
Bowling? Really?

23:54.417 --> 23:57.625
[ LAUGHS ]
WHAT, LIKE FRED FLINTSTONE?

23:57.625 --> 24:00.959
I'M MORE IN THE BARNEY RUBBLE
CATEGORY.

24:00.959 --> 24:05.083
HOW FUN.
I'D LOVE TO WATCH YOU BOWL.

24:05.083 --> 24:08.542
IT'S NOT REALLY
A SPECTATOR SPORT.

24:08.542 --> 24:11.917
Oh, well,
I'll close my eyes.

24:11.917 --> 24:14.834
BUT IT'S SORT OF
THE GUYS' NIGHT OUT.

24:14.834 --> 24:18.083
Come on, Dexter,
I want to meet your friends.

24:18.083 --> 24:21.959
WHERE IS IT? WHAT TIME IS IT?
GIVE ME THE ADDRESS.

24:21.959 --> 24:23.834
[ SIGHS ]

24:23.834 --> 24:27.166
STARLIGHT LANES.
1690 MICHIGAN AVENUE.

24:27.166 --> 24:28.667
7:00.

24:30.792 --> 24:34.250
I GUESS I'M GOING BOWLING.

24:34.250 --> 24:37.500
[ CREEDENCE CLEARWATER REVIVAL'S
"BAD MOON RISING" PLAYING ]

24:38.959 --> 24:40.333
GO, DEXTER!

24:40.333 --> 24:44.125
♪ I SEE THE BAD MOON RISING ♪
YAY!

24:44.125 --> 24:46.125
HE ONLY GOT
THREE PINS DOWN.

24:46.125 --> 24:48.959
YEAH, WELL, I LIKE TO CELEBRATE
THE LITTLE THINGS IN LIFE.

24:48.959 --> 24:50.834
HEY, IF YOU LIKE LITTLE THINGS,
I'M YOUR MAN.

24:50.834 --> 24:52.542
I MEAN, I'M NOT LITTLE
EVERYWHERE.

24:52.542 --> 24:55.250
SOME PLACES I'M JUST
PERFECTLY AVERAGE.

24:55.250 --> 24:58.709
YOU ARE
PERFECTLY ADORABLE.

24:58.709 --> 24:59.959
[ SIGHS ]

24:59.959 --> 25:02.875
HOW COME YOU GOT A HUG
AND I GOT A PAT ON THE NOSE?

25:02.875 --> 25:05.041
'CAUSE YOU'RE LIKE
A RETARDED PUPPY.

25:11.834 --> 25:15.542
YOUR ASS DOES THE CUTEST LITTLE
THING WHEN YOU BOWL.

25:15.542 --> 25:16.834
OH, THANK YOU.

25:16.834 --> 25:18.041
[ GIGGLES ]

25:18.041 --> 25:22.709
IF YOU GUYS WILL EXCUSE ME,
I NEED TO USE THE LADIES' ROOM.

25:22.709 --> 25:27.500
♪ HOPE YOU GOT QUITE
THE PARADISE ♪

25:27.500 --> 25:30.875
SHE'S PRETTY HOT.

25:30.875 --> 25:33.166
YES. SHE IS.

25:33.166 --> 25:34.333
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

25:34.333 --> 25:36.625
[ LIGHT PIANO MUSIC PLAYS ]

25:40.583 --> 25:43.000
WOW.

25:43.000 --> 25:46.083
NICE PLACE.

25:46.083 --> 25:49.333
VERY, UH...

25:49.333 --> 25:50.875
GRAY.

25:50.875 --> 25:52.333
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:52.333 --> 25:54.583
YES, THE BUREAU
HAVE ALWAYS BEEN KNOWN

25:54.583 --> 25:56.333
FOR THEIR FASHION SENSE.

25:56.333 --> 26:00.208
HONESTLY, ALL I CARE
ABOUT IS THE KITCHEN.

26:00.208 --> 26:01.834
YOU COOK?

26:01.834 --> 26:06.959
LIKE I SAID,
BEST RESTAURANT IN MIAMI.

26:06.959 --> 26:11.625
REALLY?
YOU'RE GONNA COOK FOR ME.

26:11.625 --> 26:15.500
WELL, DON'T EVER EXPECT ME
TO RETURN THE FAVOR...

26:15.500 --> 26:18.458
UNLESS YOU'RE A BIG FAN
OF TOAST.

26:18.458 --> 26:21.875
I WOULD LOVE  TO EAT
YOUR TOAST.

26:21.875 --> 26:24.166
[ LAUGHS ]
GOSH, THAT SOUNDED WRONG.

26:24.166 --> 26:25.333
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:25.333 --> 26:26.834
SO, WHAT'S FOR DINNER?

26:26.834 --> 26:30.709
UH, STEAK FLORENTINE AND
GRILLED POTATOES ITALIAN-STYLE.

26:30.709 --> 26:32.125
FUCKING-A.

26:32.125 --> 26:33.875
THERE'S THAT MOUTH AGAIN.

26:33.875 --> 26:36.333
OH, I'M SORRY.

26:36.333 --> 26:39.166
IT'S JUST THE WAY I TALK.

26:39.166 --> 26:42.000
AND IF WE'RE GONNA BE TOGETHER,
YOU BETTER GET USED TO IT.

26:42.000 --> 26:43.375
CAN'T CHANGE WHO I AM.

26:43.375 --> 26:47.458
I'M CRASS AND DIRTY,
AND...

26:47.458 --> 26:50.792
I HAVE A VERY FILTHY MIND.

26:50.792 --> 26:52.917
YOU'RE ALSO
PRETTY ADORABLE.

26:52.917 --> 26:54.291
I KNOW.

26:54.291 --> 26:56.542
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:56.542 --> 26:58.000
NOW START
PEELING POTATOES.

26:58.000 --> 27:00.000
OOH!

27:00.000 --> 27:02.792
I LIKE A MAN
THAT TAKES CONTROL.

27:06.333 --> 27:09.792
WASH YOUR HANDS FIRST.

27:09.792 --> 27:12.291
YOU'RE SO TURNING ME ON.

27:12.291 --> 27:14.542
YOU KNOW, CONSIDERING
OUR AGE DIFFERENCE,

27:14.542 --> 27:16.458
YOU'RE NOT TOO OLD
TO SPANK.

27:16.458 --> 27:18.458
NO, STOP. PLEASE.

27:18.458 --> 27:21.166
[ Chuckling ]
I CAN'T CONTROL MYSELF.

27:21.166 --> 27:22.917
OH, MY GOD!

27:36.000 --> 27:38.750
Batista: YOU SURE YOU DON'T WANT
TO GRAB A BEER WITH US, DEXTER?

27:38.750 --> 27:41.834
NAH, THANKS. I'M TIRED.

27:41.834 --> 27:43.583
[ SMOOCHING ]

27:46.750 --> 27:51.834
MMM, I HOPED YOU SAVED
ENOUGH ENERGY FOR ME.

27:51.834 --> 27:53.875
THAT DOESN'T EXACTLY LOOK LIKE
THE LOOK OF LOVE.

27:53.875 --> 27:55.667
I'M SORRY.
I REALLY AM TIRED.

27:55.667 --> 27:57.875
DEXTER!

27:57.875 --> 28:00.625
HELP! HELP, PLEASE!

28:01.917 --> 28:03.458
SOMEBODY PLEASE COME!

28:03.458 --> 28:04.625
HEY!

28:08.166 --> 28:09.333
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

28:09.333 --> 28:11.208
Dexter: GOD.

28:14.041 --> 28:15.333
YOU OKAY?

28:15.333 --> 28:17.083
YEAH, YEAH.

28:17.083 --> 28:20.208
DEXTER, YOU'RE BLEEDING.
IT'S NOT DEEP.

28:20.208 --> 28:21.458
I MEAN, WHAT THE HELL?

28:21.458 --> 28:23.208
HE TRIED TO GRAB MY WATCH.

28:23.208 --> 28:25.208
IT'S STUPID. I SHOULD
HAVE LET HIM HAVE IT.

28:25.208 --> 28:27.375
IT WAS JUST --
IT WAS REFLEX.

28:27.375 --> 28:28.583
AS LONG AS YOU'RE OKAY.

28:28.583 --> 28:30.000
YEAH, YEAH. I'M FINE.

28:30.000 --> 28:31.875
JESUS CHRIST.

28:31.875 --> 28:33.875
THEY SELL ANYONE A GUN
IN FLORIDA, WON'T THEY?

28:33.875 --> 28:35.792
YEAH, I KNOW.
SCARY, RIGHT?

28:35.792 --> 28:37.291
ANYONE GET
A LICENSE PLATE?

28:37.291 --> 28:38.875
NO, IT WAS ALL TOO FAST.

28:38.875 --> 28:41.208
YOU WANT US TO TAKE YOU
TO A DOCTOR?
NO.

28:41.208 --> 28:43.041
REALLY, I'M FINE.

28:43.041 --> 28:44.750
I'LL TAKE CARE OF HIM.

28:50.208 --> 28:53.959
SO, WHO WAS IT?

28:53.959 --> 28:55.542
WHO?

28:55.542 --> 28:57.834
THAT MAN.
HE WASN'T TRYING TO ROB YOU.

28:57.834 --> 28:59.834
HE WAS TRYING TO KILL YOU.

29:02.458 --> 29:05.333
SANTOS JIMINEZ, THE MAN
WHO MURDERED MY MOTHER.

29:05.333 --> 29:06.500
OH, MY GOD, DEXTER.

29:06.500 --> 29:09.208
HE MUST HAVE FOLLOWED ME
TO THE BOWLING ALLEY.

29:09.208 --> 29:11.625
[ SIGHS ]

29:11.625 --> 29:13.750
IF YOU HADN'T HAVE SEEN HIM
IN TIME --

29:13.750 --> 29:16.959
Shh! I DID SEE HIM.
THAT'S ALL THAT MATTERS.

29:20.917 --> 29:24.417
NONE OF THIS SCARES YOU?

29:24.417 --> 29:29.208
NOTHING YOU COULD DO, DEXTER,
WOULD SCARE ME.

29:32.417 --> 29:34.583
I BELIEVE YOU.

29:37.208 --> 29:38.583
COME HERE.

29:42.417 --> 29:44.750
WHATEVER COMES,

29:44.750 --> 29:48.750
WE'LL GET THROUGH
THIS TOGETHER.

29:48.750 --> 29:52.500
I'M NOT LEAVING YOUR SIDE,
DEXTER.

29:52.500 --> 29:55.000
I'M NOT LEAVING YOURS.

29:56.750 --> 29:58.500
REALLY?

30:03.625 --> 30:06.792
WHY WOULD YOU THINK THAT?

30:06.792 --> 30:11.125
YOU'VE JUST BEEN
A BIT DISTANT LATELY.

30:11.125 --> 30:14.208
I GET THAT WAY
WHEN I'M STRESSED.

30:14.208 --> 30:16.417
WHAT ARE YOU
STRESSED ABOUT?

30:16.417 --> 30:17.792
[ SIGHS ]

30:20.625 --> 30:22.917
RIGHT NOW, NOTHING.

30:31.125 --> 30:35.625
DO YOU THINK DEXTER WILL COME
FOR BREAKFAST TOMORROW?

30:35.625 --> 30:39.750
OH, I-I DON'T THINK SO,
HONEY.

30:39.750 --> 30:43.291
WELL,
MAYBE WE SHOULD CALL HIM.

30:43.291 --> 30:45.583
IT'S KIND OF LATE.

30:45.583 --> 30:48.375
BUT DEXTER STAYS UP LATE.

30:48.375 --> 30:50.166
SHE DOESN'T WANT
TO CALL HIM.

30:51.333 --> 30:53.125
WHY NOT?

30:53.125 --> 30:56.333
DEXTER AND I BROKE UP.

30:56.333 --> 30:58.083
WHY?

30:58.083 --> 31:00.500
THEY DON'T LIKE
EACH OTHER ANYMORE.

31:00.500 --> 31:02.667
WELL, THAT'S NOT TRUE.

31:04.834 --> 31:08.583
DOES THAT MEAN HE DOESN'T
LIKE US, EITHER?

31:08.583 --> 31:12.875
OH, NO.
OF COURSE HE LIKES YOU.

31:12.875 --> 31:18.458
IT'S JUST...IT'S HARD
WHEN TWO PEOPLE BREAK UP.

31:18.458 --> 31:22.041
IT MAKES THEM SAD
TO SEE EACH OTHER.

31:22.041 --> 31:24.542
I DON'T THINK DEXTER'S
GONNA BE COMING FOR BREAKFAST

31:24.542 --> 31:26.166
FOR A WHILE.

31:29.750 --> 31:31.542
SORRY.

31:33.000 --> 31:34.875
LILA MAY BE THE RIGHT WOMAN
FOR ME,

31:34.875 --> 31:36.792
BUT SHE'S WRONG
ABOUT ONE THING.

31:36.792 --> 31:39.375
RECOVERY SIMPLY
ISN'T AN OPTION.

31:39.375 --> 31:40.709
WHEN I LET MY GUARD DOWN,

31:40.709 --> 31:43.500
I OPEN MYSELF UP FOR ATTACK
OR CAPTURE.

31:43.500 --> 31:46.750
I NEED TO EMBRACE WHO I AM,
WHO I'VE ALWAYS BEEN.

31:46.750 --> 31:49.834
I NEED TO KILL THE MAN
WHO MURDERED MY MOTHER.

31:54.834 --> 31:58.417
I'D ALMOST FORGOTTEN
THIS FEELING --

31:58.417 --> 32:03.709
DRIVING TOWARD A KILL,
ALL MY SENSES SHARPENED.

32:03.709 --> 32:06.250
IT'S LIKE I'VE BEEN
LIVING UNDERWATER,

32:06.250 --> 32:09.583
HOLDING MY BREATH,
AND NOW I CAN FINALLY BREATHE.

32:11.583 --> 32:14.083
SO HOW COME
IT'S SO SUFFOCATING IN HERE?

32:21.500 --> 32:23.500
LaGuerta: JAMES.

32:23.500 --> 32:25.125
HEY.

32:25.125 --> 32:27.333
HEY.
IT'S NICE TO SEE YOU.

32:27.333 --> 32:30.583
YEAH, FEELS ALL WARM
AND COMFY.

32:30.583 --> 32:33.208
I SPOKE TO TODD ABOUT YOU.

32:33.208 --> 32:34.333
YEAH?

32:34.333 --> 32:37.166
HE'S VERY INTERESTED.

32:37.166 --> 32:39.542
HE SAID SOMEONE WITH
YOUR SPECIAL-OPS BACKGROUND

32:39.542 --> 32:42.291
TYPICALLY STARTS
AT ABOUT $200,000.

32:42.291 --> 32:43.792
I COULD LIVE WITH THAT.

32:43.792 --> 32:47.542
YOU CAN MEET HIM TONIGHT.
9:00, BAR AT THE HILTON.

32:47.542 --> 32:48.959
I'LL BE THERE.

32:55.709 --> 33:00.083
SERGEANT DOAKES.
I APPRECIATE YOUR TIME.

33:00.083 --> 33:03.333
CAN WE GET THIS
OVER WITH, SIR?

33:03.333 --> 33:05.667
OKAY.

33:05.667 --> 33:08.291
IT'S INTERESTING
THAT OF THE 18 VICTIMS,

33:08.291 --> 33:10.125
9 PASSED THROUGH
THIS VERY STATION,

33:10.125 --> 33:13.417
AND YOU WORKED ON CASES
INVOLVING 4 OF THEM.

33:13.417 --> 33:16.542
AND YOU WERE UNABLE TO OBTAIN
A SINGLE CONVICTION.

33:16.542 --> 33:17.959
THE SMITH CASE THROWN OUT

33:17.959 --> 33:20.125
BECAUSE OF INADMISSIBLE
EVIDENCE.

33:20.125 --> 33:23.625
OROZCO SKIPPED BAIL,
NEVER TO BE SEEN AGAIN.

33:23.625 --> 33:27.125
THE RODRIGO CASE --
LOST DUE TO BAD BLOODWORK.

33:27.125 --> 33:29.667
EXCUSE ME?

33:29.667 --> 33:33.000
OH, YOU WEREN'T AWARE
OF THAT?

33:33.000 --> 33:34.667
THE D.A. DIDN'T GET
A CONVICTION.

33:34.667 --> 33:36.125
THAT'S ALL I KNOW.

33:38.959 --> 33:41.166
ARE WE THROUGH HERE, SIR?

33:41.166 --> 33:44.291
NO, ACTUALLY.
WE'RE JUST GETTING --
WE'RE DONE.

33:53.792 --> 33:55.583
LOOK AT THIS.

33:55.583 --> 33:58.875
"JUNE 1st -- MRS. HOLCOMB
TAKES OUT TRASH,

33:58.875 --> 34:02.792
DROPS SODA BOTTLE,
DOESN'T PICK IT UP."

34:02.792 --> 34:06.625
"MARCH 17th --
AIRPLANE FLYING TOO LOW."

34:06.625 --> 34:09.000
I TOLD YOU,
THIS GUY'S A FRUIT BAT.

34:09.000 --> 34:13.208
"APRIL."
HEY, IT'S THE MONTH WE WANT.

34:14.959 --> 34:18.000
"APRIL 16th"...

34:18.000 --> 34:20.417
FUCK ME SIDEWAYS,
LISTEN TO THIS.

34:20.417 --> 34:22.500
"RODRIGO GETS INTO CAR
PARKED IN WRONG SPACE.

34:22.500 --> 34:24.709
MUST BE DRUNK BECAUSE
SOMEONE IS CARRYING HIM."

34:24.709 --> 34:26.041
THE LICENSE PLATE'S
RIGHT HERE.

34:26.041 --> 34:28.041
THIS IS FROM 9:00
THE NIGHT HE DISAPPEARED.

34:28.041 --> 34:29.709
THE LAST TIME ANYONE
SAW HIM ALIVE.

34:29.709 --> 34:30.917
WE GOT TO RUN THAT PLATE.

34:30.917 --> 34:32.709
I BET WHOEVER OWNED THIS
FUCKING CAR IS OUR KILLER.

34:32.709 --> 34:33.875
I'M GONNA GET LUNDY.

34:33.875 --> 34:35.125
HE'S OUT WITH HIS FEDS.

34:35.125 --> 34:36.667
WELL, I'M CALLING HIM IN.

34:42.583 --> 34:47.667
LILA ALMOST HAD ME BELIEVING
IT WAS POSSIBLE TO CHANGE,

34:47.667 --> 34:50.333
TO BECOME SOMETHING ELSE,

34:50.333 --> 34:53.375
AS IF THAT EVER REALLY HAPPENS.

34:53.375 --> 34:57.333
I'VE ALWAYS KNOWN WHAT I AM.

34:57.333 --> 34:59.542
IF THE GLOVE FITS...

35:14.208 --> 35:17.458
[ ENGINES TURN OVER ]

36:26.667 --> 36:31.375
A SECRET CABIN IN THE MIDDLE
OF THE EVERGLADES --

36:31.375 --> 36:35.291
WHAT MORE COULD A REDEDICATED
SERIAL KILLER ASK FOR?

36:48.250 --> 36:50.333
COCAINE.

36:50.333 --> 36:53.875
APPARENTLY MR. JIMINEZ NEVER
GAVE UP HIS OLD HABITS.

36:53.875 --> 36:57.041
WHAT A BAD, BAD MAN.

37:04.458 --> 37:06.583
[ LATIN MUSIC PLAYS ON RADIO  ]

37:06.583 --> 37:10.750
♪ OTRA VEZ,
UNO, DOS, TRES, CUATRO  ♪

37:13.166 --> 37:15.333
♪ CUMBIA QUITA  ♪

37:15.333 --> 37:18.834
♪ CU-CUMBIA, QUE CU-CUMBIA,
QUE CU-CUMBIA  ♪

37:18.834 --> 37:21.041
♪ MíRAME  ♪

37:21.041 --> 37:22.500
♪ BAILAREMOS  ♪
[ GRUNTS ]

37:22.500 --> 37:26.083
♪ CU-CUMBIA, QUE CU-CUMBIA,
QUE CU-CUMBIA  ♪

37:26.083 --> 37:27.333
♪ MíRAME  ♪

37:27.333 --> 37:30.917
WHAT, YOU THINK IT JUST
TURNED ON BY ITSELF?

37:30.917 --> 37:33.792
[ COMPUTER KEYS CLACKING ]

37:33.792 --> 37:36.917
UGH,
"THERE IS NO SUCH PLATE."

37:36.917 --> 37:39.583
IS THAT A 1 OR AN "I"?
FUCK YOU, LENNY.

37:39.583 --> 37:41.458
FUCK YOUR HANDWRITING.

37:46.750 --> 37:48.417
DEBRA.

37:48.417 --> 37:50.083
KIND OF BUSY HERE.

37:50.083 --> 37:53.458
THEN CAN YOU PLEASE TELL ME
WHERE I CAN FIND DEXTER?

37:53.458 --> 37:55.208
I BROUGHT HIM SOME DINNER.

37:55.208 --> 37:56.625
DEXTER'S NOT HERE.

37:56.625 --> 37:57.834
WHERE IS HE?

37:57.834 --> 37:59.041
HOW SHOULD I KNOW?

37:59.041 --> 38:01.375
HE SAID HE WAS
WORKING LATE.

38:03.000 --> 38:05.375
IS THAT WHAT HE TOLD YOU?

38:05.375 --> 38:07.625
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

38:07.625 --> 38:10.041
HE'S NOT WORKING LATE.

38:11.583 --> 38:14.250
I THINK HE LIED TO YOU.

38:14.250 --> 38:16.125
OH, MEN ARE SUCH PIGS.

38:16.125 --> 38:17.333
[ ELEVATOR DINGS ]

38:20.792 --> 38:22.917
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:22.917 --> 38:24.333
[ SIGHS ]

38:26.959 --> 38:29.291
I'M SO SORRY.
I'M SURE HE'LL SHOW UP.

38:29.291 --> 38:31.750
HE'S VERY EXCITED
ABOUT THIS JOB.

38:34.333 --> 38:36.083
[ SCRAPING ]

39:04.417 --> 39:05.500
[ SIGHS ]

39:05.500 --> 39:07.208
I SWEAR, I'VE TRIED
EVERY COMBINATION.

39:07.208 --> 39:10.000
NOTHING IS COMING UP.

39:10.000 --> 39:12.834
I TOLD YOU LENNY WOULD BE
A WASTE OF TIME.

39:12.834 --> 39:14.959
MAYBE IT'S NOT
A FLORIDA PLATE.

39:18.000 --> 39:20.792
TRY GEORGIA.

39:21.834 --> 39:23.500
HOLY SHIT, HERE IT IS.

39:23.500 --> 39:27.000
THE VEHICLE WAS REGISTERED
TO CHARLIE LEWIS.

39:27.000 --> 39:28.834
I KNOW THAT NAME.

39:28.834 --> 39:31.750
A DRUG DEALER
OUT OF NEW YORK.

39:31.750 --> 39:33.333
A TOUGH GUY --

39:33.333 --> 39:35.375
LIKES TO CARRY
A BIG-ASS KNIFE.

39:35.375 --> 39:37.667
THAT'S OUR GUY.
THAT'S THE BAY HARBOR BUTCHER.

39:37.667 --> 39:40.959
I TOLD YOU HE WASN'T A COP.

39:40.959 --> 39:43.125
WHAT?

39:43.125 --> 39:44.583
SHIT.

39:44.583 --> 39:46.667
WHERE IS HE?

39:46.667 --> 39:49.792
ACCORDING TO THIS,
SOUTH BAY CORRECTIONAL FACILITY.

39:49.792 --> 39:50.834
FOR HOW LONG?

39:50.834 --> 39:53.208
OH, SHIT.

39:53.208 --> 39:56.458
CHARLIE LEWIS WAS ARRESTED
APRIL 12, 2002.

39:56.458 --> 39:58.333
THAT'S FOUR DAYS
BEFORE RODRIGO WAS SEEN

39:58.333 --> 39:59.959
BEING CARRIED
INTO THE CAR.

39:59.959 --> 40:01.583
WHO HAD HIS CAR?
ONE OF HIS GANG?

40:01.583 --> 40:03.375
THIS IS WHERE IT GETS
REALLY BAD.

40:03.375 --> 40:04.875
THE VEHICLE WAS SEIZED
AS EVIDENCE.

40:04.875 --> 40:06.542
BY WHO?

40:06.542 --> 40:08.625
BY OUR  DEPARTMENT.

40:08.625 --> 40:11.333
WHERE WAS
THE VEHICLE HELD?

40:11.333 --> 40:14.625
RIGHT HERE IN OUR EVIDENCE LAB,
BEHIND A SECURE GATE.

40:14.625 --> 40:17.542
SOMEONE SIGNED THE VEHICLE OUT,
PICKED RODRIGO UP,

40:17.542 --> 40:20.041
KILLED HIM, AND THEN SIGNED
THE VEHICLE BACK IN.

40:20.041 --> 40:21.333
SO YOU HAVE RECORDS.

40:21.333 --> 40:23.083
WHY WOULD WE KEEP THEM?

40:23.083 --> 40:25.583
THE ONLY PEOPLE ALLOWED ACCESS
TO THOSE VEHICLES

40:25.583 --> 40:28.041
ARE MEMBERS OF THE MIAMI METRO
POLICE DEPARTMENT.

40:28.041 --> 40:29.542
HOLY SHIT.

40:32.417 --> 40:36.542
BAY HARBOR BUTCHER
IS ONE OF OUR OWN.

40:38.375 --> 40:41.083
WE KEEP THIS TO OURSELVES
FOR NOW --

40:41.083 --> 40:42.417
JUST THE THREE OF US.

40:42.417 --> 40:45.417
I'M GONNA GO TELL IT
TO A BOTTLE OF SCOTCH.

41:07.125 --> 41:09.125
[ INDISTINCT TALKING
IN DISTANCE ]

41:09.125 --> 41:10.792
[ VEHICLE PASSING ]

41:24.667 --> 41:27.083
HERE WE ARE AGAIN.

41:27.083 --> 41:30.667
WHAT -- WHAT THE FUCK?!

41:30.667 --> 41:35.000
I KNOW. I KEEP ASKING MYSELF
THAT SAME QUESTION.

41:43.208 --> 41:45.250
LET ME OUT OF HERE!

41:45.250 --> 41:46.792
BUT...

41:46.792 --> 41:51.166
I'M FINDING IT'S BEST TO ACCEPT
THINGS YOU CAN'T CHANGE,

41:51.166 --> 41:52.542
YOU KNOW?

41:52.542 --> 41:55.667
NORMALLY, I'D HAVE A CHAT

41:55.667 --> 41:59.000
TO MAKE SURE YOU UNDERSTAND
WHY YOU'RE HERE, BUT...

41:59.000 --> 42:03.291
I THINK YOU HAVE
A PRETTY GOOD IDEA.

42:03.291 --> 42:05.583
LET ME GO.

42:05.583 --> 42:08.125
I GOT COCAINE.

42:08.125 --> 42:10.375
YOU CAN HAVE ALL OF IT.

42:10.375 --> 42:15.250
IT'S FUNNY YOU SHOULD SAY THAT.
I AM OFF THE WAGON.

42:15.250 --> 42:18.333
BUT THAT WAS NEVER MY DRUG.

42:18.333 --> 42:22.667
I'LL FUCKING KILL  YOU!

42:22.667 --> 42:24.291
[ TAPE TEARS ]

42:27.125 --> 42:28.667
NO, MR. JIMINEZ.

42:28.667 --> 42:32.667
I'M GONNA
KILL YOU  TONIGHT...

42:32.667 --> 42:35.917
FOR WHAT YOU DID
TO MY MOTHER...

42:35.917 --> 42:40.333
AND BECAUSE, WELL,
THIS IS WHAT I DO BEST.

42:48.458 --> 42:51.041
IT'S KIND OF FITTING,
DON'T YOU THINK?

42:51.041 --> 42:52.959
[ ENGINE REVS ]

42:52.959 --> 42:55.542
[ REVVING ]

42:57.208 --> 42:58.917
[ MOANING ]

43:16.875 --> 43:20.083
Rita: ASTOR, CODY,
COME ON, LET'S EAT.

43:23.208 --> 43:25.333
HOW'D YOU GET
THE DOOR UNLOCKED?

43:25.333 --> 43:28.166
IT WAS ALREADY OPEN.

43:28.166 --> 43:30.041
OH, THAT'S ODD.

43:36.917 --> 43:39.208
[ AIR-CONDITIONER TURNS ON ]

43:45.125 --> 43:46.792
[ FAN STOPS ]

43:52.125 --> 43:54.250
[ RATTLING ]

44:19.375 --> 44:21.750
[ SIGHS ]

44:50.166 --> 44:51.625
LILA.

44:51.625 --> 44:53.375
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

45:00.417 --> 45:02.083
HELLO?

45:02.083 --> 45:03.625
DEXTER, HI.

45:03.625 --> 45:05.542
UM, LOOK,
I'M SORRY TO BOTHER YOU,

45:05.542 --> 45:07.208
AND I'M SURE
THIS IS NOTHING,

45:07.208 --> 45:10.083
BUT I WAS JUST WONDERING IF
BY CHANCE YOU WERE AT MY HOUSE.

45:10.083 --> 45:12.250
UH, WELL, NO.

45:12.250 --> 45:13.792
Well, it's just
that the door was open

45:13.792 --> 45:16.375
AND YOU'RE THE ONLY OTHER ONE
WITH A KEY.

45:20.500 --> 45:22.709
RITA, GET OUT OF THE HOUSE.
CALL THE POLICE.

45:22.709 --> 45:24.750
I'LL BE THERE AS SOON AS I CAN.

45:29.291 --> 45:32.417
I CAN'T LEAVE YOU HERE.

45:32.417 --> 45:35.709
I CAN'T TAKE YOU WITH ME.

45:35.709 --> 45:38.000
DON'T GO ANYWHERE!

45:40.291 --> 45:43.750
OH, HEY, I'M SORRY TO DRAG
YOU INTO THIS.

45:43.750 --> 45:45.709
NO, NO, I'M GLAD YOU CALLED.
THE KIDS?

45:45.709 --> 45:47.208
NEXT DOOR.

45:49.792 --> 45:53.208
THE PLACE IS EMPTY.
NO SIGN OF FORCIBLE ENTRY.

45:53.208 --> 45:56.500
I'M GUESSING YOU JUST FORGOT
TO LOCK THE DOOR.

45:56.500 --> 45:58.041
IF YOU NEED
ANYTHING ELSE --

45:58.041 --> 45:59.291
NO, NO.
YOU'RE NOT LEAVING.

45:59.291 --> 46:00.625
SIR?

46:00.625 --> 46:02.166
SOMEONE WAS
IN THIS HOUSE.

46:02.166 --> 46:04.250
I NEED YOU TO STAY HERE
IN THE HOUSE

46:04.250 --> 46:05.750
UNTIL I TELL YOU IT'S SAFE.

46:05.750 --> 46:08.166
REALLY? I NEED  TO DO
THOSE THINGS.

46:08.166 --> 46:09.583
I'M WITH MIAMI
METRO HOMICIDE.

46:09.583 --> 46:11.083
I KNOW YOU DON'T TAKE ORDERS
FROM ME,

46:11.083 --> 46:12.208
BUT IF YOU'D LIKE,

46:12.208 --> 46:13.750
I COULD GET LIEUTENANT LaGUERTA
ON THE PHONE.

46:13.750 --> 46:15.750
OR IF YOU PREFER TO SPEAK
TO CAPTAIN MATTHEWS,

46:15.750 --> 46:17.291
I COULD ARRANGE THAT,
AS WELL.

46:17.291 --> 46:19.125
DEXTER, WHAT'S GOING ON?

46:19.125 --> 46:21.542
PLEASE,
JUST STAY HERE, OKAY?

46:23.083 --> 46:25.125
IT'S ONE THING
TO FUCK WITH ME,

46:25.125 --> 46:29.458
ANOTHER TO FUCK WITH MY
EX-GIRLFRIEND WHO HATES ME.

46:29.458 --> 46:32.750
THE LILA EXPERIMENT
IS OFFICIALLY OVER.

46:32.750 --> 46:35.166
DEXTER!

46:35.166 --> 46:37.417
GIVE ME RITA'S KEY.

46:41.250 --> 46:44.458
WELL, THAT'S YOUR FAULT,
ISN'T IT, DEXTER?

46:44.458 --> 46:47.792
YOU LIED  TO ME
ABOUT WORKING LATE,

46:47.792 --> 46:51.041
AND I THOUGHT I MIGHT
FIND YOU THERE.

46:51.041 --> 46:54.417
DO NOT EVER  GO
TO RITA'S HOUSE AGAIN.

46:54.417 --> 46:56.709
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

46:56.709 --> 47:00.250
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

47:00.250 --> 47:01.875
OH.

47:01.875 --> 47:05.041
IS THIS THE MONSTER THAT YOU
KEEP TELLING ME ABOUT?

47:05.041 --> 47:08.083
TRUST ME, WHEN YOU MEET
THE MONSTER, YOU'LL KNOW.

47:11.333 --> 47:14.458
YOU CALLED JIMINEZ.

47:14.458 --> 47:16.125
YEAH, I SUPPOSE I DID.

47:16.125 --> 47:18.875
WHY?

47:18.875 --> 47:21.083
WHY WOULD YOU TRY
TO HAVE ME KILLED?

47:21.083 --> 47:22.875
YOU WEREN'T GOING
TO GET KILLED.

47:22.875 --> 47:25.083
THAT'S WHY I DID IT
AT THE BOWLING ALLEY,

47:25.083 --> 47:27.959
SO ALL YOUR POLICE-OFFICER
FRIENDS WOULD BE THERE.

47:27.959 --> 47:30.792
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?!
ARE YOU INSANE?!

47:30.792 --> 47:33.792
I WAS TRYING TO BRING US
BACK TOGETHER AGAIN!

47:33.792 --> 47:37.959
YOU WERE PULLING AWAY,
AND...

47:37.959 --> 47:43.250
REMEMBER AT THE HOTEL
AFTER YOU FACED JIMINEZ?

47:43.250 --> 47:47.417
THAT --
THAT'S WHAT I WANTED!

47:47.417 --> 47:51.166
TO BRING YOU BACK.

47:51.166 --> 47:55.000
SO YOU CALLED HIM?

47:55.000 --> 47:58.250
WELL, IT WORKED,
DIDN'T IT?

47:58.250 --> 48:01.333
LAST NIGHT. YOU AND I.

48:01.333 --> 48:04.041
YOU FELL ASLEEP IN MY ARMS.

48:07.792 --> 48:11.000
WHAT?!

48:13.291 --> 48:15.000
YOU --

48:15.000 --> 48:20.375
YOU ARE MORE DANGEROUS
THAN MY ADDICTION WILL EVER BE.

48:20.375 --> 48:22.041
THAT'S SAYING A LOT.

48:25.375 --> 48:28.667
STAY AWAY FROM RITA.

48:28.667 --> 48:32.500
STAY AWAY FROM ME.

48:32.500 --> 48:35.041
OR WHAT?

48:36.667 --> 48:39.166
OR YOU WILL  SEE THE MONSTER.
